clients, users, projects, aiOperations, documents, invoices, support, governance, analytics. Keep it small and readable. Do not use axios unless already used; fetch is fine. Ensure code is client-safe and does not break SSR. Run frontend lint/build.\"\n","success":true},{"query":"git grep -ni \"supabase\" || true","result":"automation/logs/2026-06-26T17-35-40-274Z-43-phase3-blueprint-wizard-inputs-review.log:715:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-26T17:35:22.881Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"run_commands\",\"toolCallId\":\"xq9w9sro\",\"output\":[{\"query\":\"git diff automation/tasks.json\",\"result\":\"diff --git a/automation/tasks.json b/automation/tasks.json\\nindex 88fa391..19554da 100644\\n--- a/automation/tasks.json\\n+++ b/automation/tasks.json\\n@@ -550,5 +550,429 @@\\n     \\\"target\\\": \\\"entire Phase 3 interactive layer\\\",\\n     \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n     \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 3 interactive Build With GFF tools. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Verify shared tool architecture works. Verify frontend-only safety: no backend, no AWS, no auth, no real OTP, no real email, no database, no real API calls, no real exports. Verify Blueprint scoring and Banking example 87/100. Verify assessment and ROI calculations are deterministic and labelled illustrative. Verify local workspace does not break hydration. Verify mobile responsiveness, accessibility, reduced motion, command center deep actions, links, CTAs, empty states, error states, result states, and visual polish. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for the next backend/FastAPI phase.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"69-phase4-preflight-portal-admin-audit\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Phase 4 preflight audit for login admin and client portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-audit\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login admin client portal frontend\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"This is the first task of Phase 4. Do not edit files. Audit the current implementation for all login, client portal, admin portal, and private workspace related routes and components. Inspect app/portal, app/client, app/admin if present, app/login if present, app/layout.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/CommandCenter.tsx, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, and any existing dashboard, portal, auth, client, admin, table, document, billing, support, analytics, or governance components. Determine what currently exists as a public shell and what is missing for a proper logged-in product experience. Do not create backend, real auth, database, AWS, email, OTP, payment, upload, or API integrations. Produce a detailed implementation gap report for Phase 4 frontend. The report must cover required routes, app shell, local auth preview, role switching, route protection preview, client portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, admin dashboard, client management, user management, project management, documents admin, billing admin, support admin, analytics admin, governance admin, activity feed, notifications, global search, command center, tables, filters, mobile UX, accessibility, design system, and final QA. Final response must include files inspected, existing capabilities, missing routes, missing components, design risks, and recommended implementation order. Do not edit files.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"70-phase4-private-app-design-system\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create private app design system for portal and admin\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-foundation\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"private app design primitives\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the shared private app design system for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch the public landing page. Do not redesign public pages. This task should create or improve reusable frontend-only UI primitives for authenticated-style product screens. The UI must feel like a premium 2026 enterprise AI operations product, not a generic admin template. Follow the public website theme but make the private workspace feel more operational, secure, data-rich, and product-grade. Create only necessary reusable components, such as PrivateAppShell, PrivateSidebar, PrivateTopbar, PrivatePageHeader, WorkspaceBreadcrumbs, WorkspaceCommandButton, WorkspaceCard, MetricTile, StatusBadge, DataTable, FilterBar, EmptyState, ActivityFeed, Timeline, DocumentCard, InvoiceCard, SupportTicketCard, AnalyticsPanel, GovernancePanel, AgentHealthCard, ProjectCard, UserAvatar, NotificationBell, RoleSwitcherPreview, and SecurePreviewNotice if useful. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired effects locally, such as subtle spotlight cards, moving borders, bento dashboards, animated tabs, sticky sidebars, and command palette surfaces. Do not install heavy dependencies without approval. All components must be responsive, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and scoped so they do not affect the public landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"71-phase4-private-route-map\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create explicit routes for login client portal and admin portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-routing\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"private route structure\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create or verify explicit App Router pages for the full Phase 4 route structure. Do not use slug routing. Do not create app/[...slug]/page.tsx. Do not recreate PublicRoutePage. Do not touch the landing page. Required public entry routes: /login, /portal, /portal/login. Required client portal routes: /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/projects/[id] if the current project supports dynamic explicit folders safely, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/ai-operations/[id] if safe, /portal/documents, /portal/documents/[id] if safe, /portal/billing, /portal/billing/invoices, /portal/billing/invoices/[id] if safe, /portal/support, /portal/support/[id] if safe, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /portal/settings, /portal/activity. Required compatibility client routes: /client, /client/control-center, /client/dashboard if useful. Required admin routes: /admin, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/clients/[id] if safe, /admin/projects, /admin/projects/[id] if safe, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance, /admin/settings, /admin/activity. If dynamic routes are risky in the current automation, create explicit list/detail pages without dynamic params and use local state/detail drawers instead. Pages may initially render shared shell placeholders, but every route must exist explicitly. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"72-phase4-local-auth-session-rbac-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build local auth session and role-based preview layer\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-auth-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"frontend-only auth and RBAC preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build a frontend-only local auth/session preview layer for Phase 4. Do not add real authentication. Do not call APIs. Do not add backend, cookies requiring server auth, JWT verification, OAuth, Cognito, Firebase, Clerk, Supabase, or database. Implement a safe local preview system using localStorage or in-memory state with hydration guards. Support roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. Provide local preview users with clearly fake/internal preview labels, not real identities. Add helper utilities such as getPreviewSession, setPreviewSession, clearPreviewSession, hasRole, canAccessPortalSection, canAccessAdminSection. Add safe route guard components that redirect or show a locked preview state when no local preview session exists. Every message must say this is frontend preview only and real auth will be connected in backend phase. Do not make it look like real security. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"73-phase4-client-login-landing\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Login public landing at /portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal public client login landing\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Upgrade /portal into a premium Client Login landing page. This page is public and should explain the secure delivery workspace before login. Do not touch the main landing page. /portal must contain module previews: Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. It should have a premium login CTA, secure workspace narrative, module preview cards, trust/security style visual language without fake certifications, and a clear note that login/auth is frontend preview only in this phase. Add route links to /portal/login and preview module anchors or cards. Design should feel expensive, secure, enterprise-grade, and consistent with the GFF AI theme. Use polished graphics, bento cards, dashboard previews without fake data, and subtle motion. No real auth, no API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"74-phase4-login-page\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium login page and local role preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build premium frontend-only login pages for /login and /portal/login. Do not touch landing page. The login UI should feel like a secure enterprise product login, with GFF AI branding, email field, password field placeholder, SSO button placeholders, OTP login placeholder, role preview selector for local development, and clear frontend-only notice. On submit, create a local preview session only and route client roles to /portal/dashboard and GFF/admin roles to /admin/dashboard. Do not implement real auth, password validation beyond simple required fields, OTP sending, SSO, OAuth, sessions, cookies, JWT, backend calls, or API calls. Add forgot password placeholder link and contact support link. Make it mobile excellent, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and visually premium with subtle motion. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"75-phase4-forgot-password-otp-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build forgot password and OTP preview states\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login recovery frontend preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add frontend-only forgot password and OTP preview states to the login experience. Do not create real password reset, email, OTP, or backend calls. The forgot password UI should allow entering an email and then show a safe preview message: password reset will be connected in the backend authentication phase. The OTP UI should allow entering a 6 digit placeholder code only for preview and must not pretend to send or verify real OTP. Add accessible validation, clear microcopy, and safe reset/back actions. The UI should be polished and secure-looking but honest. Do not touch landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"76-phase4-private-app-shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build private workspace app shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-layout\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"shared client and admin app shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the shared private app shell used by client portal and admin portal pages. Do not touch landing page. The shell should include a responsive sidebar, topbar, workspace switcher or organization label, breadcrumb area, global search trigger, notification bell, user menu, role preview indicator, sign out preview action, and content container. The sidebar should support grouped navigation and collapse behavior on desktop, bottom or drawer navigation on mobile, and clear active states. Client portal navigation must include Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Admin navigation must include Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Make the UI feel like a premium enterprise control center, not a basic admin template. Use current theme, subtle motion, accessible landmarks, keyboard focus, and mobile-first behavior. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"77-phase4-private-mock-data-model\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create local mock data model for portal and admin\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-data\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"local mock data\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create a local mock data model for the client portal and admin portal. Do not add a database or backend. Do not create fake real customer data that implies actual clients. Use clearly representative data and label it as preview/demo data where surfaced. Data should support dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing/invoices, support tickets, analytics, governance, users, clients, activity feed, and notifications. Include types for ClientAccount, Project, Program, AgentOperation, AgentHealth, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, AnalyticsMetric, GovernanceItem, Approval, User, Role, ActivityEvent, Notification. Include deterministic sample entries such as representative client account, representative project names, representative agent names, preview invoices, preview tickets. No fake logos or real client names. Centralize in a safe local data file. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"78-phase4-data-table-filter-system\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium data table filter and list system\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-component\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"tables lists filters\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build reusable premium table, list, filter, and detail-drawer components for portal and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Components should support search, status filters, type filters, date range placeholder, sort controls, empty state, row click, selected state, pagination or local visible count, mobile card fallback, and accessible keyboard navigation. Use these components for Projects, Documents, Billing, Support, Users, Clients, AI Operations, Governance, and Activity. Make the design feel custom and expensive, not default HTML tables. Use subtle row hover, sticky header where useful, and clean responsive cards on mobile. No backend calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"79-phase4-client-dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/dashboard as the main client portal cockpit. Do not touch landing page. Use the private app shell. The dashboard should include welcome header, account summary, active projects, AI operations status, document updates, billing snapshot, open support tickets, analytics highlights, governance alerts, recent activity, and next actions. Use representative preview data only, no fake live data. Dashboard widgets should be visually premium, with bento layout, metric tiles, progress visuals, status cards, timeline, and CTA cards. Metrics must be clearly preview/demo if they could be mistaken as real. Add links to Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance. Mobile must stack beautifully. Use motion lightly. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"80-phase4-client-projects-list\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Projects list\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/projects\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/projects as a premium project and program management view for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include project cards or table with search, status filters, phase filters such as Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, owner, timeline, progress, next milestone, and health status. Use representative preview data only. Include empty state and local detail drawer if dynamic route is not used. UI should feel like a high-end enterprise delivery dashboard. Add CTA to request update or contact support using frontend-only action. No backend. Mobile card view required. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"81-phase4-client-project-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Project detail experience\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"project detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the client project detail experience using /portal/projects/[id] if the current route architecture supports it, otherwise use a detail drawer from /portal/projects. Do not touch landing page. Project detail must include overview, project phase, scope, timeline, milestones, squad, deliverables, linked documents, approvals, support items, AI operations connected to the project, recent activity, and next steps. Include tabs: Overview, Timeline, Deliverables, Team, Documents, Activity. Use representative preview data only. Make it polished, narrative, and operational with timeline visuals and progress indicators. No API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"82-phase4-client-ai-operations-overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal AI Operations overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/ai-operations\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/ai-operations as the client-facing AI operations command center. Do not touch landing page. Include agent health overview, managed AI operations status, active agents, human review queue preview, governance checks, runtime status, adoption indicators, spend preview, incident/issue preview, and Control Center link. Use labels and representative preview data only. Do not claim real-time operations. Use premium dashboard UI with status rails, agent cards, health rings, timeline, and tabs. Add filters by project, agent type, status, and operating stage. No backend. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"83-phase4-client-ai-operation-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal AI operation detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"AI operation detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build AI operation detail experience using /portal/ai-operations/[id] if safe, otherwise use a detail drawer from /portal/ai-operations. Do not touch landing page. Detail must include agent purpose, linked project, health status, recent runs preview, human approval points, governance controls, knowledge sources, issue log, adoption notes, and suggested actions. This is frontend preview only and must not imply live agent runtime. Use a premium observability style with tabs: Summary, Workflow, Governance, Activity, Documents. Include SVG/CSS workflow graphic. No backend. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"84-phase4-client-documents-library\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Documents library\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/documents\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/documents as a premium document library for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include document search, category filters, project filters, document type filters, status filters, recent uploads preview, pinned documents, and document cards/table. Categories may include Proposals, SOW, Architecture, Reports, Invoices, Governance, Meeting Notes, Delivery Assets. No real file upload or download. Add disabled or preview upload button with future backend note. Add document preview drawer with metadata, related project, version, owner, and activity. Use representative data only. Mobile must be excellent. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"85-phase4-client-document-detail-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Document detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"document detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build a document detail preview experience using /portal/documents/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from the documents page. Do not touch landing page. Include metadata, version history preview, related project, approvals, activity, file status, and related documents. Do not render real PDFs or require file storage. If a preview area is shown, make it a static styled placeholder saying file preview will be connected in the backend storage phase. No real upload/download. Design must feel secure and professional. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"86-phase4-client-billing-overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Billing and invoices\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/billing and /portal/billing/invoices\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/billing and /portal/billing/invoices as premium billing and invoice preview pages. Do not touch landing page. Include billing summary, invoice list, invoice status, due date, project association, amount preview, payment status preview, and billing contact card. Use representative preview data only. Do not integrate payments. Do not claim real invoices. Add frontend-only actions such as View invoice preview, Copy invoice reference, Contact finance, and Download disabled with backend note. Include filters and mobile card layout. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"87-phase4-client-invoice-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Invoice detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"invoice detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build invoice detail preview using /portal/billing/invoices/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from invoices. Do not touch landing page. Include invoice header, status, project, line items preview, tax/fee placeholder, due date, notes, related documents, and support CTA. No real payment, no payment provider, no PDF generation, no download. If download is shown, it must be disabled or marked future backend integration. Design should feel like a premium enterprise finance page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"88-phase4-client-support-center\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Support center\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/support\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/support as a premium support center for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include ticket list, create ticket frontend-only form, priority, category, linked project, linked document optional, status filters, support SLA preview copy without guarantees, knowledge/help cards, and recent support activity. No backend submission. On create, add ticket locally in current browser state or show preview-created state. Ticket categories: Project Delivery, AI Operations, Billing, Documents, Access, Governance, General. UI should feel calm, secure, and operational. Mobile excellent. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"89-phase4-client-support-ticket-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Support ticket detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"support ticket detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build support ticket detail experience using /portal/support/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from support center. Do not touch landing page. Include ticket summary, status, priorit\n[... output truncated: 187913 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nng\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Login public landing at /portal\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal public client login landing\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Upgrade /portal into a premium Client Login landing page. This page is public and should explain the secure delivery workspace before login. Do not touch the main landing page. /portal must contain module previews: Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. It should have a premium login CTA, secure workspace narrative, module preview cards, trust/security style visual language without fake certifications, and a clear note that login/auth is frontend preview only in this phase. Add route links to /portal/login and preview module anchors or cards. Design should feel expensive, secure, enterprise-grade, and consistent with the GFF AI theme. Use polished graphics, bento cards, dashboard previews without fake data, and subtle motion. No real auth, no API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"74-phase4-login-page\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium login page and local role preview\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build premium frontend-only login pages for /login and /portal/login. Do not touch landing page. The login UI should feel like a secure enterprise product login, with GFF AI branding, email field, password field placeholder, SSO button placeholders, OTP login placeholder, role preview selector for local development, and clear frontend-only notice. On submit, create a local preview session only and route client roles to /portal/dashboard and GFF/admin roles to /admin/dashboard. Do not implement real auth, password validation beyond simple required fields, OTP sending, SSO, OAuth, sessions, cookies, JWT, backend calls, or API calls. Add forgot password placeholder link and contact support link. Make it mobile excellent, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and visually premium with subtle motion. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login recovery frontend preview\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add frontend-only forgot password and OTP preview states to the login experience. Do not create real password reset, email, OTP, or backend calls. The forgot password UI should allow entering an email and then show a safe preview message: password reset will be connected in the backend authentication phase. The OTP UI should allow entering a 6 digit placeholder code only for preview and must not pretend to send or verify real OTP. Add accessible validation, clear microcopy, and safe reset/back actions. The UI should be polished and secure-looking but honest. Do not touch landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Polish empty states, locked states, unauthenticated states, no-results states, and preview-only notices across login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Every empty state should explain what it means and what action is available. Locked states should be role-aware and explain permissions preview. Unauthenticated routes should show a premium sign-in required state with route to /portal/login. No scary errors. No fake backend failure. Use polished graphics and microcopy. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Improve frontend-only route guard UX for client and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. If no local preview session exists, private routes should show sign-in required or redirect safely to /portal/login depending on current app pattern. If a user has a client role and opens /admin, show access restricted preview. If an admin role opens /portal pages, allow or show switch workspace depending on chosen preview logic. Add clear role preview switcher and sign out action. Do not implement real security. Do not use backend. Ensure hydration safety. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a mobile UX pass for all login, portal, client, and admin routes. Do not touch landing page. Fix only mobile and responsive issues. Check /login, /portal, /portal/login, /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/documents, /portal/billing, /portal/support, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /portal/settings, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/projects, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance, /admin/settings. Ensure no horizontal overflow, sidebar works on mobile, topbar is usable, tables become cards, filters collapse, modals/drawers fit, charts are readable, buttons are tappable, and forms are easy to use. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Accessibility pass for login portal and admin\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform an accessibility pass for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Ensure pages have one clear H1, semantic landmarks, accessible sidebar navigation, keyboard accessible menus, focus states, labelled forms, labelled filters, accessible table/card interactions, accessible dialogs/drawers, notification dropdown accessibility, command center accessibility, reduced motion support, sufficient contrast, and correct button/link semantics. Fix only accessibility issues. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform motion and interaction polish for login, portal, and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Add subtle page transitions, sidebar active motion, card reveal, table row hover, drawer transitions, notification dropdown animation, command palette transitions, chart reveal, status card micro-interactions, and form state transitions where appropriate. Respect prefers-reduced-motion. Keep motion expensive and calm, not noisy. Do not add dependencies. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login portal admin UI\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final premium visual polish for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Improve any UI that feels generic, unfinished, repetitive, too boxy, too badge-heavy, or like a basic admin template. Make the private workspace feel like a custom 2026 enterprise AI operations product built by a senior design team. Use refined spacing, typography, bento dashboards, high-quality tables, elegant filters, strong empty states, premium charts, SVG/CSS visual panels, subtle gradients, and purposeful motion. Do not add fake data. Do not add dependencies. Preserve public site theme. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Audit and fix frontend-only safety for Phase 4. Do not touch landing page. Search for fetch, axios, app/api usage, localhost API calls, auth providers, JWT verification, Cognito, Firebase, Supabase, Clerk, AWS, S3, SES, payment providers, upload APIs, email sending, OTP sending, database imports, real file downloads, real invoice generation, and server actions. Remove or disable any accidental real integration in login, portal, admin, documents, billing, support, and analytics. All auth/session/data must be local preview only. If legacy app/api/contact exists, do not use it from Phase 4 UI. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Audit and fix all links in login, client portal, admin portal, private sidebar, topbar, command center, notifications, tables, cards, CTAs, breadcrumbs, and detail drawers. Do not touch landing page. Verify all links resolve to explicit routes. No slug route references. /portal must be the Client Login landing. /portal/login and /login must work. Client portal modules must include Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing or Invoices, Support, Analytics, Governance. Admin modules must include Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Fix broken links only. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create or update documentation for Phase 4 frontend implementation. Do not build backend. Create docs/PHASE_4_LOGIN_ADMIN_CLIENT_PORTAL.md or update existing docs. Document routes built, local auth preview behavior, roles, route guard preview, client portal modules, admin modules, local mock data, frontend-only limitations, future backend requirements, future FastAPI endpoints, future database tables, future storage needs, future email/OTP needs, future billing/payment integration, and security considerations. Clearly state that Phase 4 is frontend-only and not production authentication. Include recommended Phase 5 backend build order. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login admin client portal frontend\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 4. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /portal is a Client Login landing and contains module previews for Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. Verify /login and /portal/login work as frontend-only local preview login. Verify local roles and route guards work as previews. Verify client portal pages: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify admin pages: Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify private shell, sidebar, topbar, notifications, command center, global search, tables, filters, detail drawers, local data, empty states, locked states, mobile, accessibility, and visual polish. Verify no backend, real auth, AWS, OTP, email, database, uploads, payments, or real API calls were added. Verify no landing page files were changed. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for Phase 5 backend.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"This is the first task of Phase 5. Do not edit files. Audit the current project before creating any backend or database logic. Inspect package.json, app directory, existing app/api routes if any, middleware.ts if any, lib directory, portal/admin route tree, auth/session preview logic from Phase 4, local mock data files, private app shell, login pages, client portal pages, admin portal pages, and existing environment files. Determine the current frontend framework and safest local backend approach. Prefer using Next.js App Router route handlers under app/api if this is a Next.js app. Do not create a separate FastAPI backend in this phase unless the project already has one and it is clearly intended. Audit whether Prisma, SQLite, PostgreSQL client, zod, bcrypt, jose/jsonwebtoken, or auth libraries already exist. Produce a detailed plan for Phase 5 only: local/dev database, schema, seed data, JWT/session auth, RBAC, CRUD APIs, frontend API client, and portal/admin integration. Explicitly confirm that GFF AI tools such as Blueprint Generator, ROI Calculator, Proposal Builder, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio must remain frontend-only and must not receive backend APIs in this phase. Final response must include existing stack, recommended dev database approach, dependencies present/missing, files to avoid, backend modules to build, integration risks, and task order. Do not edit files.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create the core local/dev database schema for identity, roles, clients, and users. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. If using Prisma, define models in prisma/schema.prisma. Required concepts: User, Role, Permission or role enum, ClientAccount, ClientMembership, UserSession or Session if useful, Invite placeholder if useful, and AuditEvent or ActivityEvent base if useful. Roles must support: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. Users need id, name, email, passwordHash, role, status, clientId or memberships, createdAt, updatedAt, lastLoginAt optional. ClientAccount needs id, name, industry, region, status, accountOwner, createdAt, updatedAt. ClientMembership should support users connected to clients with role. Use dev-safe constraints and indexes where sensible. Do not create real OAuth tables. Do not add production security claims. Generate migration or local schema artifacts if required. Run schema validation and build where possible.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"129-phase5-auth-api-login-logout-me\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build auth APIs login logout and current user\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create real local/dev auth API routes for portal/admin authentication. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: POST /api/auth/login, POST /api/auth/logout, GET /api/auth/me. Optional safe route: POST /api/auth/switch-role only in development if useful, but prefer real seeded users. Login accepts email and password, validates with zod, checks password hash, sets httpOnly JWT cookie, updates lastLoginAt, creates activity event, and returns safe user profile. Logout clears cookie and creates activity event if user exists. Me returns current authenticated user, role, client memberships, permissions, and default landing route. Do not implement OTP or password reset here. Do not call external services. Add rate limit placeholder comment only, no external dependency. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create a lightweight frontend API client for portal/admin APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Add typed helper functions for GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE with consistent response handling, credentials include for cookie session, validation-friendly error handling, loading/error states, and abort safety if useful. Create auth hooks or context for current user: useCurrentUser, useLogin, useLogout, useRequireAuth, useHasRole if consistent with existing React patterns. Replace only Phase 4 local preview auth usage in login/portal/admin with real API-backed auth. Do not integrate this API client into /build Blueprint, ROI, Assessment, Proposal, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, or Talk to Agent. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"131-phase5-login-frontend-real-auth-integration\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Integrate login UI with real local auth API\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Integrate /login and /portal/login with the real local/dev auth API. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace Phase 4 local preview session login with POST /api/auth/login. On successful login, route client roles to /portal/dashboard and admin/internal roles to /admin/dashboard. Show loading, validation errors, invalid credentials, server unavailable, and success states. Keep SSO, OTP, and forgot password as disabled/future features unless already implemented as preview states. Do not implement real OTP or reset emails. Add logout integration with POST /api/auth/logout from private shell user menu. Ensure /api/auth/me powers current user display. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Replace Phase 4 frontend-only route guard preview with real session-backed protected route behavior for portal and admin pages. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Private shell should call /api/auth/me or shared auth context. Unauthenticated users should be sent to /portal/login or shown sign-in required state according to current design. Client roles should access /portal pages for their own client account. Admin/internal roles should access /admin pages based on permissions. Unauthorized access should show polished Access Restricted page, not a crash. Keep hydration safe. Remove or de-emphasize local preview role switcher from production-like UI; if kept, mark development only. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build client-facing profile/workspace APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: GET /api/portal/profile, GET /api/portal/workspace-summary. These should return current authenticated user's safe profile, client account, membership role, permissions, dashboard module availability, and workspace counts. Enforce that client users only see their own client account. Admin/internal users may preview or access based on permission if desired. No sensitive fields. Add activity event for login/session where appropriate. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build database-backed Activity APIs and server-side activity logging helpers. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: GET /api/portal/activity and GET /api/admin/activity. Activity events should be created by major APIs: login, logout, client create/update, project create/update, AI operation update, document metadata create/update, invoice create/update, support ticket create/comment/status, governance update, approval action, user create/update. Activity fields: actorId, clientId optional, projectId optional, module, action, entityType, entityId, message, metadata JSON optional, createdAt. Enforce client scoping and RBAC. Do not implement production-grade audit claims; this is local/dev app foundation. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add a lightweight API smoke test script for local/dev backend if the project structure supports it. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. The script should document or automate checks for login, /api/auth/me, client dashboard, admin dashboard, projects list, support ticket create, notification read, and logout. If fully automated HTTP testing is too heavy, create a docs-based smoke test checklist instead. Do not add heavy test frameworks unless already present. If a test framework exists, add focused tests for auth helpers, RBAC helpers, Blueprint exclusion from backend, and a few API utilities. Run available tests if safe, then lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a frontend UX pass for loading, error, empty, unauthorized, forbidden, validation, and success states across all API-integrated portal/admin pages. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Pages: login, portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, activity, admin dashboard, clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, activity. Ensure states are premium, calm, accessible, and not generic. Do not add new modules. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a mobile responsiveness pass after Phase 5 API integration. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Fix only mobile issues caused by real data/API integration. Check tables, forms, drawers, sidebar, topbar, dashboards, login, search, command center, notifications, filters, charts, and detail pages. Ensure no horizontal overflow, proper touch targets, readable cards, accessible drawers, and usable forms. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend foundation works. Verify database schema, migration/push, seed data, auth APIs, login/logout/me, JWT/session cookie, RBAC, protected routes, client portal APIs, admin APIs, CRUD flows, frontend API integration, dashboard data, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, billing/invoices without payments, support tickets/comments, analytics from local DB, governance/approvals, activity logs, notifications, settings, global search, command center session awareness, mobile, accessibility, and visual polish. Verify no AWS, S3, SES, payment provider, real uploads, real downloads, real OTP/email, external auth, or production storage was added. Verify GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and unchanged from backend perspective. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, npm test if available, and any safe db verification script if present. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, commands run, files changed in final QA, remaining warnings, and recommended Phase 6 next steps.\\\"\\ncomponents/Header.tsx:          <Link href=\\\"/portal\\\"   className=\\\"text-white text-[14px] xl:text-[16px] leading-[24px] font-medium text-[#009DFF] hover:text-red-400 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap rounded-md px-1 py-0.5 xl:pr-8\\\">CLIENT LOGIN</Link>\\ncomponents/portal/PortalHero.tsx:              href=\\\"/portal/login\\\"\\ncomponents/portal/SecureLogin.tsx:export default function SecureLogin({ defaultRole }: { defaultRole?: string }) {\\ncomponents/portal/SecureLogin.tsx:                      onClick={() => alert(\\\"SSO handshaking: Initializing secure Okta login...\\\")}\\ncomponents/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx:        setTimeout(() => router.push(\\\"/login\\\"), 800);\\ncomponents/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx:          <button onClick={() => router.push(\\\"/login\\\")} className=\\\"w-full h-10 rounded-lg bg-white text-black font-bold text-[10px] uppercase\\\">\\ncomponents/private-app/notices-avatars.tsx:                    router.push(\\\"/login\\\");\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:  const logIndexRef = useRef<number>(0);\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:      const index = logIndexRef.current;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:        logIndexRef.current = index + 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:        logIndexRef.current = 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:    logIndexRef.current = 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:    logIndexRef.current = 1;\\nlib/nav-data.ts:  { label: \\\"CLIENT LOGIN\\\", href: \\\"/portal\\\" },\\n\",\"success\":true}],\"durationMs\":1265}}\nautomation/tasks.json:584:    \"prompt\": \"Build a frontend-only local auth/session preview layer for Phase 4. Do not add real authentication. Do not call APIs. Do not add backend, cookies requiring server auth, JWT verification, OAuth, Cognito, Firebase, Clerk, Supabase, or database. Implement a safe local preview system using localStorage or in-memory state with hydration guards. Support roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin. Provide local preview users with clearly fake/internal preview labels, not real identities. Add helper utilities such as getPreviewSession, setPreviewSession, clearPreviewSession, hasRole, canAccessPortalSection, canAccessAdminSection. Add safe route guard components that redirect or show a locked preview state when no local preview session exists. Every message must say this is frontend preview only and real auth will be connected in backend phase. Do not make it look like real security. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:792:    \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix frontend-only safety for Phase 4. Do not touch landing page. Search for fetch, axios, app/api usage, localhost API calls, auth providers, JWT verification, Cognito, Firebase, Supabase, Clerk, AWS, S3, SES, payment providers, upload APIs, email sending, OTP sending, database imports, real file downloads, real invoice generation, and server actions. Remove or disable any accidental real integration in login, portal, admin, documents, billing, support, and analytics. All auth/session/data must be local preview only. If legacy app/api/contact exists, do not use it from Phase 4 UI. Run lint and build.\"\n","success":true},{"query":"git grep -ni \"firebase\" || true","result":"automation/logs/2026-06-26T17-35-40-274Z-43-phase3-blueprint-wizard-inputs-review.log:715:{\"ts\":\"2026-06-26T17:35:22.881Z\",\"type\":\"agent_event\",\"event\":{\"type\":\"content_end\",\"contentType\":\"tool\",\"toolName\":\"run_commands\",\"toolCallId\":\"xq9w9sro\",\"output\":[{\"query\":\"git diff automation/tasks.json\",\"result\":\"diff --git a/automation/tasks.json b/automation/tasks.json\\nindex 88fa391..19554da 100644\\n--- a/automation/tasks.json\\n+++ b/automation/tasks.json\\n@@ -550,5 +550,429 @@\\n     \\\"target\\\": \\\"entire Phase 3 interactive layer\\\",\\n     \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n     \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 3 interactive Build With GFF tools. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /build, /build/talk, /build/blueprint, /build/assessment, /build/roi, /build/sandbox, /build/proposal, /build/marketplace, /build/foundry-studio. Verify shared tool architecture works. Verify frontend-only safety: no backend, no AWS, no auth, no real OTP, no real email, no database, no real API calls, no real exports. Verify Blueprint scoring and Banking example 87/100. Verify assessment and ROI calculations are deterministic and labelled illustrative. Verify local workspace does not break hydration. Verify mobile responsiveness, accessibility, reduced motion, command center deep actions, links, CTAs, empty states, error states, result states, and visual polish. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for the next backend/FastAPI phase.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"69-phase4-preflight-portal-admin-audit\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Phase 4 preflight audit for login admin and client portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-audit\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login admin client portal frontend\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"This is the first task of Phase 4. Do not edit files. Audit the current implementation for all login, client portal, admin portal, and private workspace related routes and components. Inspect app/portal, app/client, app/admin if present, app/login if present, app/layout.tsx, components/Header.tsx, components/Footer.tsx, components/CommandCenter.tsx, components/Phase2PublicPages.tsx, components/Phase2InteractivePanels.tsx, lib/site-map-data.ts, lib/public-page-content.ts, lib/frontend-placeholders.ts, and any existing dashboard, portal, auth, client, admin, table, document, billing, support, analytics, or governance components. Determine what currently exists as a public shell and what is missing for a proper logged-in product experience. Do not create backend, real auth, database, AWS, email, OTP, payment, upload, or API integrations. Produce a detailed implementation gap report for Phase 4 frontend. The report must cover required routes, app shell, local auth preview, role switching, route protection preview, client portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, admin dashboard, client management, user management, project management, documents admin, billing admin, support admin, analytics admin, governance admin, activity feed, notifications, global search, command center, tables, filters, mobile UX, accessibility, design system, and final QA. Final response must include files inspected, existing capabilities, missing routes, missing components, design risks, and recommended implementation order. Do not edit files.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"70-phase4-private-app-design-system\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create private app design system for portal and admin\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-foundation\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"private app design primitives\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the shared private app design system for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch the public landing page. Do not redesign public pages. This task should create or improve reusable frontend-only UI primitives for authenticated-style product screens. The UI must feel like a premium 2026 enterprise AI operations product, not a generic admin template. Follow the public website theme but make the private workspace feel more operational, secure, data-rich, and product-grade. Create only necessary reusable components, such as PrivateAppShell, PrivateSidebar, PrivateTopbar, PrivatePageHeader, WorkspaceBreadcrumbs, WorkspaceCommandButton, WorkspaceCard, MetricTile, StatusBadge, DataTable, FilterBar, EmptyState, ActivityFeed, Timeline, DocumentCard, InvoiceCard, SupportTicketCard, AnalyticsPanel, GovernancePanel, AgentHealthCard, ProjectCard, UserAvatar, NotificationBell, RoleSwitcherPreview, and SecurePreviewNotice if useful. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Use Aceternity-inspired effects locally, such as subtle spotlight cards, moving borders, bento dashboards, animated tabs, sticky sidebars, and command palette surfaces. Do not install heavy dependencies without approval. All components must be responsive, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and scoped so they do not affect the public landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"71-phase4-private-route-map\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create explicit routes for login client portal and admin portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-routing\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"private route structure\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create or verify explicit App Router pages for the full Phase 4 route structure. Do not use slug routing. Do not create app/[...slug]/page.tsx. Do not recreate PublicRoutePage. Do not touch the landing page. Required public entry routes: /login, /portal, /portal/login. Required client portal routes: /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/projects/[id] if the current project supports dynamic explicit folders safely, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/ai-operations/[id] if safe, /portal/documents, /portal/documents/[id] if safe, /portal/billing, /portal/billing/invoices, /portal/billing/invoices/[id] if safe, /portal/support, /portal/support/[id] if safe, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /portal/settings, /portal/activity. Required compatibility client routes: /client, /client/control-center, /client/dashboard if useful. Required admin routes: /admin, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/clients/[id] if safe, /admin/projects, /admin/projects/[id] if safe, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance, /admin/settings, /admin/activity. If dynamic routes are risky in the current automation, create explicit list/detail pages without dynamic params and use local state/detail drawers instead. Pages may initially render shared shell placeholders, but every route must exist explicitly. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"72-phase4-local-auth-session-rbac-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build local auth session and role-based preview layer\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-auth-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"frontend-only auth and RBAC preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build a frontend-only local auth/session preview layer for Phase 4. Do not add real authentication. Do not call APIs. Do not add backend, cookies requiring server auth, JWT verification, OAuth, Cognito, Firebase, Clerk, Supabase, or database. Implement a safe local preview system using localStorage or in-memory state with hydration guards. Support roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. Provide local preview users with clearly fake/internal preview labels, not real identities. Add helper utilities such as getPreviewSession, setPreviewSession, clearPreviewSession, hasRole, canAccessPortalSection, canAccessAdminSection. Add safe route guard components that redirect or show a locked preview state when no local preview session exists. Every message must say this is frontend preview only and real auth will be connected in backend phase. Do not make it look like real security. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"73-phase4-client-login-landing\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Login public landing at /portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal public client login landing\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Upgrade /portal into a premium Client Login landing page. This page is public and should explain the secure delivery workspace before login. Do not touch the main landing page. /portal must contain module previews: Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. It should have a premium login CTA, secure workspace narrative, module preview cards, trust/security style visual language without fake certifications, and a clear note that login/auth is frontend preview only in this phase. Add route links to /portal/login and preview module anchors or cards. Design should feel expensive, secure, enterprise-grade, and consistent with the GFF AI theme. Use polished graphics, bento cards, dashboard previews without fake data, and subtle motion. No real auth, no API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"74-phase4-login-page\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium login page and local role preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build premium frontend-only login pages for /login and /portal/login. Do not touch landing page. The login UI should feel like a secure enterprise product login, with GFF AI branding, email field, password field placeholder, SSO button placeholders, OTP login placeholder, role preview selector for local development, and clear frontend-only notice. On submit, create a local preview session only and route client roles to /portal/dashboard and GFF/admin roles to /admin/dashboard. Do not implement real auth, password validation beyond simple required fields, OTP sending, SSO, OAuth, sessions, cookies, JWT, backend calls, or API calls. Add forgot password placeholder link and contact support link. Make it mobile excellent, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and visually premium with subtle motion. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"75-phase4-forgot-password-otp-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build forgot password and OTP preview states\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login recovery frontend preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add frontend-only forgot password and OTP preview states to the login experience. Do not create real password reset, email, OTP, or backend calls. The forgot password UI should allow entering an email and then show a safe preview message: password reset will be connected in the backend authentication phase. The OTP UI should allow entering a 6 digit placeholder code only for preview and must not pretend to send or verify real OTP. Add accessible validation, clear microcopy, and safe reset/back actions. The UI should be polished and secure-looking but honest. Do not touch landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"76-phase4-private-app-shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build private workspace app shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-layout\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"shared client and admin app shell\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the shared private app shell used by client portal and admin portal pages. Do not touch landing page. The shell should include a responsive sidebar, topbar, workspace switcher or organization label, breadcrumb area, global search trigger, notification bell, user menu, role preview indicator, sign out preview action, and content container. The sidebar should support grouped navigation and collapse behavior on desktop, bottom or drawer navigation on mobile, and clear active states. Client portal navigation must include Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Admin navigation must include Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Activity, Settings. Make the UI feel like a premium enterprise control center, not a basic admin template. Use current theme, subtle motion, accessible landmarks, keyboard focus, and mobile-first behavior. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"77-phase4-private-mock-data-model\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Create local mock data model for portal and admin\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-data\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"local mock data\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create a local mock data model for the client portal and admin portal. Do not add a database or backend. Do not create fake real customer data that implies actual clients. Use clearly representative data and label it as preview/demo data where surfaced. Data should support dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing/invoices, support tickets, analytics, governance, users, clients, activity feed, and notifications. Include types for ClientAccount, Project, Program, AgentOperation, AgentHealth, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, AnalyticsMetric, GovernanceItem, Approval, User, Role, ActivityEvent, Notification. Include deterministic sample entries such as representative client account, representative project names, representative agent names, preview invoices, preview tickets. No fake logos or real client names. Centralize in a safe local data file. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"78-phase4-data-table-filter-system\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium data table filter and list system\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-component\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"tables lists filters\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build reusable premium table, list, filter, and detail-drawer components for portal and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Components should support search, status filters, type filters, date range placeholder, sort controls, empty state, row click, selected state, pagination or local visible count, mobile card fallback, and accessible keyboard navigation. Use these components for Projects, Documents, Billing, Support, Users, Clients, AI Operations, Governance, and Activity. Make the design feel custom and expensive, not default HTML tables. Use subtle row hover, sticky header where useful, and clean responsive cards on mobile. No backend calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"79-phase4-client-dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/dashboard\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/dashboard as the main client portal cockpit. Do not touch landing page. Use the private app shell. The dashboard should include welcome header, account summary, active projects, AI operations status, document updates, billing snapshot, open support tickets, analytics highlights, governance alerts, recent activity, and next actions. Use representative preview data only, no fake live data. Dashboard widgets should be visually premium, with bento layout, metric tiles, progress visuals, status cards, timeline, and CTA cards. Metrics must be clearly preview/demo if they could be mistaken as real. Add links to Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance. Mobile must stack beautifully. Use motion lightly. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"80-phase4-client-projects-list\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Projects list\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/projects\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/projects as a premium project and program management view for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include project cards or table with search, status filters, phase filters such as Garage, Foundry, Factory, Operate, owner, timeline, progress, next milestone, and health status. Use representative preview data only. Include empty state and local detail drawer if dynamic route is not used. UI should feel like a high-end enterprise delivery dashboard. Add CTA to request update or contact support using frontend-only action. No backend. Mobile card view required. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"81-phase4-client-project-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Project detail experience\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"project detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build the client project detail experience using /portal/projects/[id] if the current route architecture supports it, otherwise use a detail drawer from /portal/projects. Do not touch landing page. Project detail must include overview, project phase, scope, timeline, milestones, squad, deliverables, linked documents, approvals, support items, AI operations connected to the project, recent activity, and next steps. Include tabs: Overview, Timeline, Deliverables, Team, Documents, Activity. Use representative preview data only. Make it polished, narrative, and operational with timeline visuals and progress indicators. No API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"82-phase4-client-ai-operations-overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal AI Operations overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/ai-operations\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/ai-operations as the client-facing AI operations command center. Do not touch landing page. Include agent health overview, managed AI operations status, active agents, human review queue preview, governance checks, runtime status, adoption indicators, spend preview, incident/issue preview, and Control Center link. Use labels and representative preview data only. Do not claim real-time operations. Use premium dashboard UI with status rails, agent cards, health rings, timeline, and tabs. Add filters by project, agent type, status, and operating stage. No backend. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"83-phase4-client-ai-operation-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal AI operation detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"AI operation detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build AI operation detail experience using /portal/ai-operations/[id] if safe, otherwise use a detail drawer from /portal/ai-operations. Do not touch landing page. Detail must include agent purpose, linked project, health status, recent runs preview, human approval points, governance controls, knowledge sources, issue log, adoption notes, and suggested actions. This is frontend preview only and must not imply live agent runtime. Use a premium observability style with tabs: Summary, Workflow, Governance, Activity, Documents. Include SVG/CSS workflow graphic. No backend. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"84-phase4-client-documents-library\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Documents library\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/documents\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/documents as a premium document library for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include document search, category filters, project filters, document type filters, status filters, recent uploads preview, pinned documents, and document cards/table. Categories may include Proposals, SOW, Architecture, Reports, Invoices, Governance, Meeting Notes, Delivery Assets. No real file upload or download. Add disabled or preview upload button with future backend note. Add document preview drawer with metadata, related project, version, owner, and activity. Use representative data only. Mobile must be excellent. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"85-phase4-client-document-detail-preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Document detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"document detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build a document detail preview experience using /portal/documents/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from the documents page. Do not touch landing page. Include metadata, version history preview, related project, approvals, activity, file status, and related documents. Do not render real PDFs or require file storage. If a preview area is shown, make it a static styled placeholder saying file preview will be connected in the backend storage phase. No real upload/download. Design must feel secure and professional. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"86-phase4-client-billing-overview\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Billing and invoices\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/billing and /portal/billing/invoices\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/billing and /portal/billing/invoices as premium billing and invoice preview pages. Do not touch landing page. Include billing summary, invoice list, invoice status, due date, project association, amount preview, payment status preview, and billing contact card. Use representative preview data only. Do not integrate payments. Do not claim real invoices. Add frontend-only actions such as View invoice preview, Copy invoice reference, Contact finance, and Download disabled with backend note. Include filters and mobile card layout. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"87-phase4-client-invoice-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Invoice detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"invoice detail preview\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build invoice detail preview using /portal/billing/invoices/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from invoices. Do not touch landing page. Include invoice header, status, project, line items preview, tax/fee placeholder, due date, notes, related documents, and support CTA. No real payment, no payment provider, no PDF generation, no download. If download is shown, it must be disabled or marked future backend integration. Design should feel like a premium enterprise finance page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"88-phase4-client-support-center\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Support center\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal/support\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build /portal/support as a premium support center for clients. Do not touch landing page. Include ticket list, create ticket frontend-only form, priority, category, linked project, linked document optional, status filters, support SLA preview copy without guarantees, knowledge/help cards, and recent support activity. No backend submission. On create, add ticket locally in current browser state or show preview-created state. Ticket categories: Project Delivery, AI Operations, Billing, Documents, Access, Governance, General. UI should feel calm, secure, and operational. Mobile excellent. Run lint and build.\\\"\\n+  },\\n+  {\\n+    \\\"id\\\": \\\"89-phase4-client-support-ticket-detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Portal Support ticket detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-client-portal\\\",\\n+    \\\"target\\\": \\\"support ticket detail\\\",\\n+    \\\"allowLandingChanges\\\": false,\\n+    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build support ticket detail experience using /portal/support/[id] if safe, otherwise a detail drawer from support center. Do not touch landing page. Include ticket summary, status, priorit\n[... output truncated: 191416 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nng\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build Client Login public landing at /portal\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/portal public client login landing\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Upgrade /portal into a premium Client Login landing page. This page is public and should explain the secure delivery workspace before login. Do not touch the main landing page. /portal must contain module previews: Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. It should have a premium login CTA, secure workspace narrative, module preview cards, trust/security style visual language without fake certifications, and a clear note that login/auth is frontend preview only in this phase. Add route links to /portal/login and preview module anchors or cards. Design should feel expensive, secure, enterprise-grade, and consistent with the GFF AI theme. Use polished graphics, bento cards, dashboard previews without fake data, and subtle motion. No real auth, no API calls. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"74-phase4-login-page\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build premium login page and local role preview\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build premium frontend-only login pages for /login and /portal/login. Do not touch landing page. The login UI should feel like a secure enterprise product login, with GFF AI branding, email field, password field placeholder, SSO button placeholders, OTP login placeholder, role preview selector for local development, and clear frontend-only notice. On submit, create a local preview session only and route client roles to /portal/dashboard and GFF/admin roles to /admin/dashboard. Do not implement real auth, password validation beyond simple required fields, OTP sending, SSO, OAuth, sessions, cookies, JWT, backend calls, or API calls. Add forgot password placeholder link and contact support link. Make it mobile excellent, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and visually premium with subtle motion. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"scope\\\": \\\"phase4-login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login recovery frontend preview\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add frontend-only forgot password and OTP preview states to the login experience. Do not create real password reset, email, OTP, or backend calls. The forgot password UI should allow entering an email and then show a safe preview message: password reset will be connected in the backend authentication phase. The OTP UI should allow entering a 6 digit placeholder code only for preview and must not pretend to send or verify real OTP. Add accessible validation, clear microcopy, and safe reset/back actions. The UI should be polished and secure-looking but honest. Do not touch landing page. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Polish empty states, locked states, unauthenticated states, no-results states, and preview-only notices across login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Every empty state should explain what it means and what action is available. Locked states should be role-aware and explain permissions preview. Unauthenticated routes should show a premium sign-in required state with route to /portal/login. No scary errors. No fake backend failure. Use polished graphics and microcopy. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Improve frontend-only route guard UX for client and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. If no local preview session exists, private routes should show sign-in required or redirect safely to /portal/login depending on current app pattern. If a user has a client role and opens /admin, show access restricted preview. If an admin role opens /portal pages, allow or show switch workspace depending on chosen preview logic. Add clear role preview switcher and sign out action. Do not implement real security. Do not use backend. Ensure hydration safety. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a mobile UX pass for all login, portal, client, and admin routes. Do not touch landing page. Fix only mobile and responsive issues. Check /login, /portal, /portal/login, /portal/dashboard, /portal/projects, /portal/ai-operations, /portal/documents, /portal/billing, /portal/support, /portal/analytics, /portal/governance, /portal/settings, /admin/dashboard, /admin/clients, /admin/projects, /admin/users, /admin/ai-operations, /admin/documents, /admin/billing, /admin/support, /admin/analytics, /admin/governance, /admin/settings. Ensure no horizontal overflow, sidebar works on mobile, topbar is usable, tables become cards, filters collapse, modals/drawers fit, charts are readable, buttons are tappable, and forms are easy to use. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Accessibility pass for login portal and admin\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform an accessibility pass for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Ensure pages have one clear H1, semantic landmarks, accessible sidebar navigation, keyboard accessible menus, focus states, labelled forms, labelled filters, accessible table/card interactions, accessible dialogs/drawers, notification dropdown accessibility, command center accessibility, reduced motion support, sufficient contrast, and correct button/link semantics. Fix only accessibility issues. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform motion and interaction polish for login, portal, and admin pages. Do not touch landing page. Use Framer Motion or motion/react only if already installed. Add subtle page transitions, sidebar active motion, card reveal, table row hover, drawer transitions, notification dropdown animation, command palette transitions, chart reveal, status card micro-interactions, and form state transitions where appropriate. Respect prefers-reduced-motion. Keep motion expensive and calm, not noisy. Do not add dependencies. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login portal admin UI\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final premium visual polish for login, client portal, and admin portal. Do not touch landing page. Improve any UI that feels generic, unfinished, repetitive, too boxy, too badge-heavy, or like a basic admin template. Make the private workspace feel like a custom 2026 enterprise AI operations product built by a senior design team. Use refined spacing, typography, bento dashboards, high-quality tables, elegant filters, strong empty states, premium charts, SVG/CSS visual panels, subtle gradients, and purposeful motion. Do not add fake data. Do not add dependencies. Preserve public site theme. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Audit and fix frontend-only safety for Phase 4. Do not touch landing page. Search for fetch, axios, app/api usage, localhost API calls, auth providers, JWT verification, Cognito, Firebase, Supabase, Clerk, AWS, S3, SES, payment providers, upload APIs, email sending, OTP sending, database imports, real file downloads, real invoice generation, and server actions. Remove or disable any accidental real integration in login, portal, admin, documents, billing, support, and analytics. All auth/session/data must be local preview only. If legacy app/api/contact exists, do not use it from Phase 4 UI. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Audit and fix all links in login, client portal, admin portal, private sidebar, topbar, command center, notifications, tables, cards, CTAs, breadcrumbs, and detail drawers. Do not touch landing page. Verify all links resolve to explicit routes. No slug route references. /portal must be the Client Login landing. /portal/login and /login must work. Client portal modules must include Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing or Invoices, Support, Analytics, Governance. Admin modules must include Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings. Fix broken links only. Run lint and build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create or update documentation for Phase 4 frontend implementation. Do not build backend. Create docs/PHASE_4_LOGIN_ADMIN_CLIENT_PORTAL.md or update existing docs. Document routes built, local auth preview behavior, roles, route guard preview, client portal modules, admin modules, local mock data, frontend-only limitations, future backend requirements, future FastAPI endpoints, future database tables, future storage needs, future email/OTP needs, future billing/payment integration, and security considerations. Clearly state that Phase 4 is frontend-only and not production authentication. Include recommended Phase 5 backend build order. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"login admin client portal frontend\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 4. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify /portal is a Client Login landing and contains module previews for Dashboard, Projects, Invoices or Billing, Support, Documents, AI Operations, Analytics, Governance. Verify /login and /portal/login work as frontend-only local preview login. Verify local roles and route guards work as previews. Verify client portal pages: Dashboard, Projects, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify admin pages: Dashboard, Clients, Projects, Users, AI Operations, Documents, Billing, Support, Analytics, Governance, Settings, Activity. Verify private shell, sidebar, topbar, notifications, command center, global search, tables, filters, detail drawers, local data, empty states, locked states, mobile, accessibility, and visual polish. Verify no backend, real auth, AWS, OTP, email, database, uploads, payments, or real API calls were added. Verify no landing page files were changed. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for Phase 5 backend.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"This is the first task of Phase 5. Do not edit files. Audit the current project before creating any backend or database logic. Inspect package.json, app directory, existing app/api routes if any, middleware.ts if any, lib directory, portal/admin route tree, auth/session preview logic from Phase 4, local mock data files, private app shell, login pages, client portal pages, admin portal pages, and existing environment files. Determine the current frontend framework and safest local backend approach. Prefer using Next.js App Router route handlers under app/api if this is a Next.js app. Do not create a separate FastAPI backend in this phase unless the project already has one and it is clearly intended. Audit whether Prisma, SQLite, PostgreSQL client, zod, bcrypt, jose/jsonwebtoken, or auth libraries already exist. Produce a detailed plan for Phase 5 only: local/dev database, schema, seed data, JWT/session auth, RBAC, CRUD APIs, frontend API client, and portal/admin integration. Explicitly confirm that GFF AI tools such as Blueprint Generator, ROI Calculator, Proposal Builder, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, and Foundry Studio must remain frontend-only and must not receive backend APIs in this phase. Final response must include existing stack, recommended dev database approach, dependencies present/missing, files to avoid, backend modules to build, integration risks, and task order. Do not edit files.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create the core local/dev database schema for identity, roles, clients, and users. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. If using Prisma, define models in prisma/schema.prisma. Required concepts: User, Role, Permission or role enum, ClientAccount, ClientMembership, UserSession or Session if useful, Invite placeholder if useful, and AuditEvent or ActivityEvent base if useful. Roles must support: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. Users need id, name, email, passwordHash, role, status, clientId or memberships, createdAt, updatedAt, lastLoginAt optional. ClientAccount needs id, name, industry, region, status, accountOwner, createdAt, updatedAt. ClientMembership should support users connected to clients with role. Use dev-safe constraints and indexes where sensible. Do not create real OAuth tables. Do not add production security claims. Generate migration or local schema artifacts if required. Run schema validation and build where possible.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"129-phase5-auth-api-login-logout-me\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Build auth APIs login logout and current user\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create real local/dev auth API routes for portal/admin authentication. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: POST /api/auth/login, POST /api/auth/logout, GET /api/auth/me. Optional safe route: POST /api/auth/switch-role only in development if useful, but prefer real seeded users. Login accepts email and password, validates with zod, checks password hash, sets httpOnly JWT cookie, updates lastLoginAt, creates activity event, and returns safe user profile. Logout clears cookie and creates activity event if user exists. Me returns current authenticated user, role, client memberships, permissions, and default landing route. Do not implement OTP or password reset here. Do not call external services. Add rate limit placeholder comment only, no external dependency. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Create a lightweight frontend API client for portal/admin APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Add typed helper functions for GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE with consistent response handling, credentials include for cookie session, validation-friendly error handling, loading/error states, and abort safety if useful. Create auth hooks or context for current user: useCurrentUser, useLogin, useLogout, useRequireAuth, useHasRole if consistent with existing React patterns. Replace only Phase 4 local preview auth usage in login/portal/admin with real API-backed auth. Do not integrate this API client into /build Blueprint, ROI, Assessment, Proposal, Sandbox, Marketplace, Foundry Studio, or Talk to Agent. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"id\\\": \\\"131-phase5-login-frontend-real-auth-integration\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Integrate login UI with real local auth API\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"target\\\": \\\"/login and /portal/login\\\",\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Integrate /login and /portal/login with the real local/dev auth API. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Replace Phase 4 local preview session login with POST /api/auth/login. On successful login, route client roles to /portal/dashboard and admin/internal roles to /admin/dashboard. Show loading, validation errors, invalid credentials, server unavailable, and success states. Keep SSO, OTP, and forgot password as disabled/future features unless already implemented as preview states. Do not implement real OTP or reset emails. Add logout integration with POST /api/auth/logout from private shell user menu. Ensure /api/auth/me powers current user display. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Replace Phase 4 frontend-only route guard preview with real session-backed protected route behavior for portal and admin pages. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Private shell should call /api/auth/me or shared auth context. Unauthenticated users should be sent to /portal/login or shown sign-in required state according to current design. Client roles should access /portal pages for their own client account. Admin/internal roles should access /admin pages based on permissions. Unauthorized access should show polished Access Restricted page, not a crash. Keep hydration safe. Remove or de-emphasize local preview role switcher from production-like UI; if kept, mark development only. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build client-facing profile/workspace APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: GET /api/portal/profile, GET /api/portal/workspace-summary. These should return current authenticated user's safe profile, client account, membership role, permissions, dashboard module availability, and workspace counts. Enforce that client users only see their own client account. Admin/internal users may preview or access based on permission if desired. No sensitive fields. Add activity event for login/session where appropriate. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Build database-backed Activity APIs and server-side activity logging helpers. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required routes: GET /api/portal/activity and GET /api/admin/activity. Activity events should be created by major APIs: login, logout, client create/update, project create/update, AI operation update, document metadata create/update, invoice create/update, support ticket create/comment/status, governance update, approval action, user create/update. Activity fields: actorId, clientId optional, projectId optional, module, action, entityType, entityId, message, metadata JSON optional, createdAt. Enforce client scoping and RBAC. Do not implement production-grade audit claims; this is local/dev app foundation. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Add a lightweight API smoke test script for local/dev backend if the project structure supports it. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. The script should document or automate checks for login, /api/auth/me, client dashboard, admin dashboard, projects list, support ticket create, notification read, and logout. If fully automated HTTP testing is too heavy, create a docs-based smoke test checklist instead. Do not add heavy test frameworks unless already present. If a test framework exists, add focused tests for auth helpers, RBAC helpers, Blueprint exclusion from backend, and a few API utilities. Run available tests if safe, then lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a frontend UX pass for loading, error, empty, unauthorized, forbidden, validation, and success states across all API-integrated portal/admin pages. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Pages: login, portal dashboard, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, activity, admin dashboard, clients, users, projects, AI operations, documents, billing, support, analytics, governance, settings, activity. Ensure states are premium, calm, accessible, and not generic. Do not add new modules. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform a mobile responsiveness pass after Phase 5 API integration. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Fix only mobile issues caused by real data/API integration. Check tables, forms, drawers, sidebar, topbar, dashboards, login, search, command center, notifications, filters, charts, and detail pages. Ensure no horizontal overflow, proper touch targets, readable cards, accessible drawers, and usable forms. Run lint/build.\\\"\\nautomation/tasks.json:    \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Perform final QA for Phase 5. Do not add new features unless fixing a small clear issue. Verify local/dev backend foundation works. Verify database schema, migration/push, seed data, auth APIs, login/logout/me, JWT/session cookie, RBAC, protected routes, client portal APIs, admin APIs, CRUD flows, frontend API integration, dashboard data, projects, AI operations, documents metadata, billing/invoices without payments, support tickets/comments, analytics from local DB, governance/approvals, activity logs, notifications, settings, global search, command center session awareness, mobile, accessibility, and visual polish. Verify no AWS, S3, SES, payment provider, real uploads, real downloads, real OTP/email, external auth, or production storage was added. Verify GFF AI tools remain frontend-only and unchanged from backend perspective. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, npm test if available, and any safe db verification script if present. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, commands run, files changed in final QA, remaining warnings, and recommended Phase 6 next steps.\\\"\\ncomponents/Header.tsx:          <Link href=\\\"/portal\\\"   className=\\\"text-white text-[14px] xl:text-[16px] leading-[24px] font-medium text-[#009DFF] hover:text-red-400 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap rounded-md px-1 py-0.5 xl:pr-8\\\">CLIENT LOGIN</Link>\\ncomponents/portal/PortalHero.tsx:              href=\\\"/portal/login\\\"\\ncomponents/portal/SecureLogin.tsx:export default function SecureLogin({ defaultRole }: { defaultRole?: string }) {\\ncomponents/portal/SecureLogin.tsx:                      onClick={() => alert(\\\"SSO handshaking: Initializing secure Okta login...\\\")}\\ncomponents/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx:        setTimeout(() => router.push(\\\"/login\\\"), 800);\\ncomponents/private-app/PreviewRouteGuard.tsx:          <button onClick={() => router.push(\\\"/login\\\")} className=\\\"w-full h-10 rounded-lg bg-white text-black font-bold text-[10px] uppercase\\\">\\ncomponents/private-app/notices-avatars.tsx:                    router.push(\\\"/login\\\");\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:  const logIndexRef = useRef<number>(0);\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:      const index = logIndexRef.current;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:        logIndexRef.current = index + 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:        logIndexRef.current = 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:    logIndexRef.current = 1;\\ncomponents/sections/ClientSuccessSection.tsx:    logIndexRef.current = 1;\\nlib/nav-data.ts:  { label: \\\"CLIENT LOGIN\\\", href: \\\"/portal\\\" },\\n\",\"success\":true}],\"durationMs\":1265}}\nautomation/tasks.json:584:    \"prompt\": \"Build a frontend-only local auth/session preview layer for Phase 4. Do not add real authentication. Do not call APIs. Do not add backend, cookies requiring server auth, JWT verification, OAuth, Cognito, Firebase, Clerk, Supabase, or database. Implement a safe local preview system using localStorage or in-memory state with hydration guards. Support roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin. Provide local preview users with clearly fake/internal preview labels, not real identities. Add helper utilities such as getPreviewSession, setPreviewSession, clearPreviewSession, hasRole, canAccessPortalSection, canAccessAdminSection. Add safe route guard components that redirect or show a locked preview state when no local preview session exists. Every message must say this is frontend preview only and real auth will be connected in backend phase. Do not make it look like real security. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:792:    \"prompt\": \"Audit and fix frontend-only safety for Phase 4. Do not touch landing page. Search for fetch, axios, app/api usage, localhost API calls, auth providers, JWT verification, Cognito, Firebase, Supabase, Clerk, AWS, S3, SES, payment providers, upload APIs, email sending, OTP sending, database imports, real file downloads, real invoice generation, and server actions. Remove or disable any accidental real integration in login, portal, admin, documents, billing, support, and analytics. All auth/session/data must be local preview only. If legacy app/api/contact exists, do not use it from Phase 4 UI. Run lint and build.\"\n","success":true}],"durationMs":506}}
