 and contact support link. Make it mobile excellent, accessible, keyboard-friendly, and visually premium with subtle motion. Run lint and build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:888:    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP auth endpoints under /api/v1/auth. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Required endpoints: POST /api/v1/auth/login, GET /api/v1/auth/me, POST /api/v1/auth/logout. Login should accept email and password, verify user, and return JWT access token plus current user info. Me should require bearer token and return current user without hashed password. Logout can be frontend-token-discard only and return success. Do not implement refresh tokens unless very small and safe. Do not implement registration, OTP, forgot password, email, OAuth, SSO, or production cookies. Include clear error handling for invalid credentials and inactive users. Run backend check.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1016:    \"prompt\": \"Connect /login and /portal/login to the MVP backend auth endpoints. Do not touch landing page. Do not modify GFF AI tools. Replace or wrap the Phase 4 local preview login so users can login against /api/v1/auth/login when backend is configured. Store access token in localStorage for MVP dev only with clear TODO for production httpOnly cookie/session hardening. Call /api/v1/auth/me to load current user. Preserve role preview fallback only if backend is unavailable, clearly labelled dev fallback. Sign out should clear token/session and route to /portal/login. Do not add OAuth, OTP, email, SSO, or production cookies. Run lint/build.\"\nautomation/tasks.json:1144:    \"prompt\": \"Create or update docs/PHASE_5_SECURITY_LIMITATIONS.md. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Document MVP security limitations honestly: JWT in localStorage or dev storage, SQLite local DB, local seed users, no production password reset, no MFA, no refresh token hardening, no httpOnly secure cookie implementation unless already done, no rate limiting, no audit-grade logs, no production RBAC review, no file scanning, no payment compliance. Document required Phase 6 hardening steps: production database, httpOnly secure cookies or hardened session strategy, refresh token rotation, password reset, MFA/SSO optional, rate limiting, audit logs, secrets management, deployment config, CORS hardening. Run lint/build if docs affect build.\"\ndocs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md:356:**Purpose**: Verifies the dispatched One-Time Password against cached Redis entries. If valid, generates a secure, HTTP-only cookie and JWT Access Token to authenticate all subsequently protected platform requests.\npackage-lock.json:5273:    \"node_modules/cookie\": {\npackage-lock.json:5275:      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/cookie/-/cookie-0.7.2.tgz\",\npackage-lock.json:5282:    \"node_modules/cookie-signature\": {\npackage-lock.json:5284:      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/cookie-signature/-/cookie-signature-1.2.2.tgz\",\npackage-lock.json:6453:        \"cookie\": \"^0.7.1\",\npackage-lock.json:6454:        \"cookie-signature\": \"^1.2.1\",\n","success":true}],"durationMs":817}}
